  "title": "A Common Thread",
  "summary": "In Plaxton's Fountain Square on Caspar, the restless ex-Imperial physician Lynae Cassius shares a cafe table with the gruff old surgeon Xar'on Tanner while they wait on a tech. Recognizing him as 'the' Doctor Tanner, whose banned comparative-physiology research she once relied on as an Imperial combat medic, Lynae draws out his bitterness: the Empire perverted his work into bioweapons and species-specific pacification, driving him to resign. As they spar over theory versus complicity, Tanner cuts through her post-defection malaise with hard-won wisdom, telling Lynae to stop being an officer and simply be a doctor, because healing is in her blood, not in anyone's orders. The conversation steadies her resolve to recover her lost love of the work, and Tanner hands over a datachip detailing an upcoming surgical procedure before departing, glass still lodged in his palm, with a wink.",
